# Single-Slit Diffraction

We simulate the intensity:

\[
I(\theta) = I_0 \left( \frac{\sin \beta}{\beta} \right)^2,
\qquad
\beta = \frac{\pi a}{\lambda} \sin \theta
\]

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

λ = 500e-9
a = 50e-6
L = 1
θ = np.linspace(-0.02, 0.02, 2000)
β = (np.pi * a / λ) * np.sin(θ)
I = (np.sin(β) / (β + 1e-20))**2

plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
plt.plot(L*np.tan(θ), I)
plt.xlabel("y on screen (m)")
plt.ylabel("Intensity")
plt.title("Single-Slit Diffraction Pattern")
plt.grid()
plt.show()
